        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>Aug 1&#47;53</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p>In accordance with a notice in the last<lb/> months occident relative to the binding of<lb/> your forth coming Bible&#44; I should wish<lb/> to have it bound at the cost of three dollars<lb/> as a <add>&#63;</add> and also to have the<lb/> name stamped in the back. I should<lb/> like to know at your earliest convenience<lb/> if there is any prospect of <persName>Dias</persName> letters<lb/> appearing in a short time as I am<lb/> anxious to posses them if there is any<lb/> prospect of them coming out in a short<lb/> time I would like you to have my<lb/> copy bound in a plain substantial manner<lb/> if <add>&#63;</add> order for an extra copy would expe&#45;<lb/>diate their appearance in any way you<lb/> can put me down for another. I am<lb/> also desirous of purchasing some Jewish<lb/> <add>&#63;</add>gical works of course in the<lb/> english language. You would oblige<lb/> me by letting me know the names<lb/> subjects and <add>&#63;</add> of such<lb/> books when if you will undertake<lb/> the <sic>ommission</sic> I will forward to you</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>the amount necessary for such purchase</p>
			<p>I have nothing to communicate in regard to<lb/> our spiritual affairs of this place as you<lb/> have a regular agent who I presume<lb/> keeps you <add>&#63;</add> to anything of importance<lb/> however I cannot close this letter without<lb/> expressing my satisfaction at the last number<lb/> of your periodical I have often regretted<add>&#63;</add><lb/> that your valuable pages should so often<lb/> be taken up with local disputes&#44; that never<lb/> interest any one out of their immediate<lb/> neighbourhood. Your article <del>of</del> on the <lb/> importance of Missions will have the affect I<lb/> am certain of <add>&#63;</add> the ages of our Brethren<lb/> to the importance in the worlds movements<lb/> upon extracts from <hi rend="underline"><persName>Grace Aguilars</persName></hi> works<lb/> are worth to me at least the years <add>&#63;</add><lb/> and I should such works to be arrogant<add>&#63;</add><lb/> those I have requested your attention to<lb/> your article on the laws of the world <placeName>Israel</placeName><add>&#63;</add><lb/> ought to be read by christians equally<lb/> with our own peoples. I could with<lb/> very little trouble to myself fill pages upon<lb/> this subject air<add>&#63;</add> or not know Dear Sir<lb/> that it would be an unfair encroachment<lb/> on your valuable time. praying for your<lb/> continued health and prosperity I<lb/> subscribe myself your most</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>obliged and Respectful<lb/> Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Henry Myers</persName></p>
			<p><placeName>Box 1515</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>St Louis Mo</placeName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Editor Occident</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
